### Tier 1 — Smart Contract (`contracts/`)

#### [NEW] [SoulboundToken.sol](file:///c:/Users/Haroon/AWT/finalpro/contracts/contracts/SoulboundToken.sol)

ERC-721-based Soulbound Token contract with:
- **Minting**: Only contract owner (university) can mint SBTs to a holder's wallet
- **Transfer disabled**: `_update` overridden to block all transfers after minting
- **Credential metadata**: Stores on-chain data (student name, degree, institution, issue date, IPFS hash for extended data)
- **Revocation**: Owner can revoke a credential (marks it invalid on-chain)
- **Re-issuance**: Owner can re-issue to same holder after revocation (key-loss recovery)
- **Verification**: Public `verifyCredential(tokenId)` returns credential state + data

#### [NEW] [deploy.js](file:///c:/Users/Haroon/AWT/finalpro/contracts/scripts/deploy.js)

Hardhat deployment script targeting local Hardhat node or testnets.

#### [NEW] [SoulboundToken.test.js](file:///c:/Users/Haroon/AWT/finalpro/contracts/test/SoulboundToken.test.js)

Comprehensive tests:
- Minting creates a token bound to the correct address
- Transfers are blocked (revert on `transferFrom`, `safeTransferFrom`)
- Only owner can mint, revoke, re-issue
- Revoked credentials are marked invalid
- Re-issuance works after revocation
- Verification returns correct data

#### [NEW] [hardhat.config.js](file:///c:/Users/Haroon/AWT/finalpro/contracts/hardhat.config.js)

Hardhat configuration with Solidity 0.8.20, local network, and optional testnet config.

---

### Tier 2 — Node.js Backend (`backend/`)

#### [NEW] [server.js](file:///c:/Users/Haroon/AWT/finalpro/backend/server.js)

Express server with CORS, JSON parsing. Connects to blockchain via ethers.js.

#### [NEW] [credentials.js](file:///c:/Users/Haroon/AWT/finalpro/backend/routes/credentials.js)

REST API endpoints:
| Method | Endpoint | Description |
|--------|----------|-------------|
| POST | `/api/credentials/issue` | Issue new SBT credential |
| POST | `/api/credentials/revoke/:tokenId` | Revoke a credential |
| POST | `/api/credentials/reissue/:tokenId` | Re-issue a revoked credential |
| GET | `/api/credentials/verify/:tokenId` | Verify credential status |
| GET | `/api/credentials/holder/:address` | Get all credentials for a wallet |
| GET | `/api/credentials/all` | List all issued credentials |

#### [NEW] [auth.js](file:///c:/Users/Haroon/AWT/finalpro/backend/middleware/auth.js)

Simple API key-based admin authentication middleware.

#### [NEW] [contract.js](file:///c:/Users/Haroon/AWT/finalpro/backend/config/contract.js)

Contract ABI loader and ethers.js contract instance factory.

---

### Tier 3 — React Frontend (`frontend/`)

#### [NEW] Vite + React app

Created via `npx create-vite@latest ./ --template react`.

#### [NEW] [VerifyCredential.jsx](file:///c:/Users/Haroon/AWT/finalpro/frontend/src/pages/VerifyCredential.jsx)

Public employer verification portal:
- Search by Token ID or wallet address
- Display credential card with status (Valid ✅ / Revoked ❌)
- Shows student name, degree, institution, issue date
- No blockchain knowledge required from the user

#### [NEW] [AdminDashboard.jsx](file:///c:/Users/Haroon/AWT/finalpro/frontend/src/pages/AdminDashboard.jsx)

University admin panel:
- Issue new credentials (form with student details + wallet address)
- View all issued credentials in a table
- Revoke / Re-issue controls per credential
- Requires API key authentication

#### [NEW] UI Components

- `Navbar.jsx` — Navigation with role-based links
- `CredentialCard.jsx` — Stylized credential display card
- `IssueForm.jsx` — Form for issuing new credentials
- `Footer.jsx` — Site footer

#### [NEW] [index.css](file:///c:/Users/Haroon/AWT/finalpro/frontend/src/index.css)

Premium design system:
